        "explanation": `Fractal is a short experimental film that explores the silent connection between nature, art, and existence through the language of patterns. The film visualizes how geometry is not only a human creation but an ancient rhythm already written into every living form, in leaves, flowers, fingerprints, and the pulse of life itself. It aims to show that creation is not separate from nature but a reflection of it, where every form repeats and connects as part of one continuous design. Fractal invites viewers to see beauty not as something invented, but as something discovered hidden in plain sight.`,
