        "output": `<iframe src="https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/1239905197/embed" allowtransparency="true" style="width: 90%; aspect-ratio: 1.2;" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen></iframe>`,
        "explanation": `<span class="bold">Concept:</span> “Amaze Life” shows the journey of a girl as she grows from childhood into adulthood. As the game progresses she faces numerous challenges and obstacles that life brings. Despite the hardships, she continues to pursue her dreams and goals. This game embodies the message that no matter what struggles we encounter, we must keep moving forward and never give up. <br><br><span class="bold">Gameplay & Structure:</span> The game is divided into four main stages, each representing a key stage of human life: <br>1. <span class="bold">Home</span> (Childhood) <br>2. <span class="bold">School</span> (School Age) <br>3. <span class="bold">Society</span> (Adulthood) <br>4. <span class="bold">Hospital/Retirement Home</span> (Old Age) <br> <br> Each stage contains three levels, with the maze growing more complex as the level per stages progresses. The increasing difficulty represents how life becomes more challenging as we age. The player must navigate through each maze, overcoming various obstacles that symbolize real-life struggles, emotions, and responsibilities.<br><br><span class="bold">Stage Breakdown & Obstacles:<br>Stage 1: Home (Childhood)</span><br><br>The first stage introduces the player to the basics of the game. This reflects the simplicity of childhood life while showing the early challenges that shape personality and growth.<br><span class="bold">Obstacles include:</span><br><br><span class="indent"> 1. Parent rules <br>2. Household chores<br>3. Broken toys<br>4. Sibling fights<br>4.Lack of freedom</span><br><br>Theme: Learning discipline and emotional understanding.<br><br><span class="bold">Stage 2: School (School age)</span><br>This stage captures the emotional rollercoaster of growing up. This includes balancing academics, friendships, and self-discovery while dealing with mental and emotional pressures.<br><br><span class="bold">Obstacles include:</span><br><br><span class="indent">1. Stress, anxiety, and depression<br>2. Loneliness<br>3. Bullying<br>4. Lack of freedom<br>5. Academic pressure<br>6. Exams and low scores<br>7. Heavy readings and deadlines<br>8. Family problems<br>9. Heartbreak<br><br>Theme: Building confidence, managing emotions, and discovering identity amidst pressure.<br><br><span class="bold">Stage 3: Society (Adulthood)</span>As the girl steps <br><br>into the real world, she faces the demands of work, relationships, and financial responsibilities. This stage tests her perseverance and personal strength.<br><span class="bold">Obstacles include:</span><br><br><span class="indent">1. Bills and financial struggles<br>2. Lack of money and debt<br>3. Sadness and burnout<br>4. Work deadlines and paperwork<br>5. Heartbreak and family problems<br>6. Gambling and alcohol addiction<br>7. Difficulty maintaining work-life balance<br>8. Pressure<br>9. Loss of purpose</span><br><br>Theme: Responsibility, perseverance, and finding balance between personal happiness and obligations.<br><br><span class="bold">Stage 4: Hospital/Retirement Home (Old Age)</span><br><br>In the final stage, the player experiences the challenges of aging and reflection on a life well-lived. Physical and emotional struggles emerge, but so does the wisdom gained through life’s journey.<br><span class="bold">Obstacles include:</span><br><br><span class="indent">1. High blood pressure<br>2. Muscle pain<br>3. Heart problems<br>4. Dementia and other illnesses<br>5. Family problems<br>6. The struggles of aging and loss<br>7. Feeling Forgotten<br>8. Sadness<br>9. Isolation</span><br><br>Theme: Acceptance, reflection, and inner peace through understanding.<br><br><span class="bold">Core Message:</span><br><br>Through perseverance and determination, the player learns that no matter how complicated the maze of life becomes, every obstacle can be overcome and every path leads to personal growth and fulfillment.<br><br><span class="bold">Link to the game:</span><br><br><a href="https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/1239905197/">Amaze Life</a><br><br><span class="bold">Instruction to play the game:</span><br><br>1. Press the green flag.<br>2. Press space to start the game.<br>3. Use Arrow keys to move the character.<br>4. Be aware of the obstacles/problems, once touched the player will go back to the original position.<br>5. Reach the goal to level up.<br>6. If you want to stop the game, press the red symbol. Note that once you press it, the game will restart from the beginning.<br><br><span class="bold">Here is a sample video of me playing the game</span><br><br><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1U_r8ilDxiFY1n4b3t0QjjZHKukYbDp1u/view?usp=sharing">Playthrough</a><br><br>Note: Some parts are cut due to the longevity of the video`,
        "biography": `Pauleen Joyce J. Buenaventura, also known as Pau, is a BS Computer Science freshman student at the University of the Philippines Los Baños. Born and raised in Santa Rosa, Nueva Ecija, she gives great importance to art as it reflects personal perspective and meaning. For her, art serves as a relief from the often demanding and exhausting world of science and technology– a space where she finds beauty and inspiration.  <br> <br> She finds joy in blending creativity with innovation, using technology as a medium to express her artistic vision. As she continues her college journey, she seeks to merge coding, design, and digital media to create projects that not only showcase her creativity but also convey meaningful messages and foster community engagement.`
